Tags:
  - 773
  - 563
By: St Augustine
---
That is chiefly to be said to Be, which always exists in one and the same way;
which is every way like itself; which can in no way be injured or changed;
which is not subject to time; which cannot at one time be other than at
another. For this is what is most truly said to Be.
